Intuition:
    To find all unique triplets that sum to zero, we sort the array first.
    Sorting helps us efficiently search pairs using two pointers and avoid duplicate triplets.

    By fixing one number and finding the remaining two numbers whose sum cancels it, we reduce the problem to a 2-sum search inside a loop.

Approach:
    Sort the array.
    Iterate through the array and fix one number nums[i].

    Skip duplicate values of nums[i] to avoid repeated triplets.

    Use two pointers (left and right) to find pairs whose sum equals -nums[i].

    If the sum is too small, move left forward; if too large, move right backward.

    When a valid triplet is found:
        Store it
        Move both pointers
        Skip duplicate values for left and right.

Complexity:
    Time complexity:O(n^2)
    Space complexity:O(1)


Code:
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> threeSum(int[] nums) {
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int n = nums.length;

        List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 2; i++) {

            // Skip duplicate first elements
            if (i > 0 && nums[i] == nums[i - 1]) continue;

            int left = i + 1;
            int right = n - 1;
            int target = -nums[i];

            while (left < right) {
                int sum = nums[left] + nums[right];

                if (sum < target) {
                    left++;
                } 
                else if (sum > target) {
                    right--;
                } 
                else {
                    result.add(Arrays.asList(nums[i], nums[left], nums[right]));

                    left++;
                    right--;

                    // Skip duplicate second element
                    while (left < right && nums[left] == nums[left - 1]) {
                        left++;
                    }

                    // Skip duplicate third element
                    while (left < right && nums[right] == nums[right + 1]) {
                        right--;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}